properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 2 at 2:06PM PST until January 4 at 1:00AM PST by NWS Medford OR
properties.description:
* WHAT...South winds 30 to 35 mph with gusts up to 55 mph
expected.

* WHERE...The Shasta Valley including Interstate I-5 between
Grenada and Weed.

* WHEN...From 4 PM Friday to 1 AM PST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Damaging winds may blow down trees and power lines.
Power outages are possible. Travel will be difficult,
especially for high profile vehicles.

* View the hazard area in detail at
https://www.wrh.noaa.gov/mfr/HAZARD
properties.instruction:
People should avoid being outside in forested areas and around
trees and branches. Use caution if you must drive.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 4 PM FRIDAY TO 1 AM PST SATURDAY
